Here is the Python version of the function:
```python
def clean_column(col):
    return col.lower().strip().replace(' ', '_').replace('-', '_')
```

The equivalent Julia code would look like this:
```julia
function clean_column(col)
    return lowercase(col).strip(' ').replace(" ", "_").replace("-", "_")
end
```

Both the Python and Julia versions of the function do essentially the same thing: They convert a string to all lower case letters, remove any leading or trailing spaces, replace spaces with underscores, and replace hyphens with underscores.
